title: History of the United States (2016–present)
added: [[Joe Biden]] is scheduled to [[Inauguration of Joe Biden|inaugurated]] on the 20th January 2021, he will be the the [[List of presidents of the United States by age|oldest President]] at 78 years old beating his predecessor Donald Trump's record of 70. His cabinet is yet to be decided aside from his Vice President, [[Kamala Harris]] (the first woman as well as the first [[African Americans|African-American]] and [[Asian Americans|Asian-American]] woman to be [[2020 United States presidential election|elected]] as [[Vice President of the United States]]) who was elected alongside Biden, yet Biden has annouced his [[COVID-19 Advisory Board]] with Co-Chairs being:
* Former [[Commissioner of Food and Drugs|Commissioner of Food and Drugs;]] [[David A. Kessler]]
* [[Yale School of Medicine]] associate dean for health equity research; [[Marcella Nunez-Smith]]
* Former [[Surgeon General of the United States]]; [[Vivek Murthy]]
